<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1348,1915]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,200,1349,1375]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Trees</emphasis>
, branches glabrous, aculeate. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[529,624,1349,1375]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Nectary</emphasis>
petiolar, sessile. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,905,1348,1374]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Stipules</emphasis>
caducous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1026,1108,1349,1375]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Leaves</emphasis>
bipinnate, paripinnate, 24–26– foliolate, leaflets opposite, oblong, venation actinodromous, translucid punctuation absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1155,1324,1384,1410]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Inflorescences</emphasis>
glomerule, axillary. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[241,336,1421,1447]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Flowers</emphasis>
sessile, actinomorphic, diplostemonous; calyx gamosepalous, sepals 5, corolla gamopetalous, tubular, white, petals 5; androecium dialystaminous, homodinamous, anthers longitudinal; ovary superior, stipitate, pluriovulate. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[285,347,1492,1518]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Fruit</emphasis>
follicle, stipulate, linear, plane, margin constricted, epicarp glabrous, black. Seeds orbicular, plane, coat black, hilum basal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
